India has a rich linguistic diversity, and the Constitution officially recognizes 22 languages. These are listed in the Eighth Schedule of the Constitution and are known as Scheduled Languages.

List of Scheduled Languages in India
Assamese

Bengali

Bodo

Dogri

Gujarati

Hindi

Kannada

Kashmiri

Konkani

Maithili

Malayalam

Manipuri (Meitei)

Marathi

Nepali

Odia

